entry.title: Russia Moves to Pull Out of Ukraine Grain Deal After Blasts Hit Crimean Port
entry.content: Russia said it would suspend participation in the export of agricultural products from Ukrainian ports, in response to an attack on the occupied Black Sea port of Sevastopol that it blamed on the government of Ukraine.

entry.title: Afghan Evacuees in Limbo While Seeking Permanent Legal Status in the U.S.
entry.content: Bipartisan legislation to grant legal status to people who fled last year’s Taliban takeover is stalled over Republicans’ security concerns.
